Philippine Stocks: Atlas, Banco de Oro, Metropolitan Bank

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-09-06T04:29:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/ayala-land-inc-banco-de-oro-dmci-philippine-stock-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 1.8 percent to
4,303.08, the sharpest loss since Aug. 9.  Banks:  Banco de Oro Unibank Inc. (BDO)  , the largest
Philippine bank by assets, sank 3.5 percent to 56.95 pesos, the
lowest since July 14, on speculation borrowing costs may decline
further after yields on  government securities  dropped to record
lows.  Metropolitan Bank & Trust (MBT)  Co, the second-
biggest, decreased 3.6 percent to 70.45 pesos, the lowest close
since June 30.  Rizal Commercial Banking Corp. (RCB)   fell 4.1
percent to 31.65 pesos, the steepest loss since Feb. 1.  Yields on the government’s 91-day, 182-day and 364-day
notes fell to the lowest levels since at least 1987 in
yesterday’s auction.  Miners:  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp decreased 2 percent to 19.20 pesos, the sharpest loss since
Aug. 17, as copper prices slid for a fourth day. Class-B shares
of  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LCB)  Co, which have no
ownership restrictions, declined 4.7 percent to 1.61 pesos.  Copper for delivery in three months declined as much as 0.8
percent to $8,891 a metric ton on the London Metal Exchange
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
